		<div class="band">
			<h3 id="band-tamarin">TAMARIN</h3>
			<img src="/public/images/band/tamarin.jpg" alt="Tamarin">

			<div class="copy">
				<p>Tamarin was the brain-child (conceived with consent) of Jon Ewen and Jez Fielder. The ultimate power duo, Tamarin brought stadium rock sound and energy in a tiny footprint to pubs, clubs and festivals throughout the South-East.</p>

				<p>Before Alien Ant Farm brought you Smooth Criminal, Tamarin brought you Nude Criminal. Before Bowling for Soup brought you …Baby One More Time, Tamarin was there yawning at how late to the party they were. With Jon Ewen on drums and lead vocals, and Jez Fielder on guitar and lead vocals, the rest of the band was canned - which at the time was very unique.</p>

				<p>After a hugely popular run with Tamarin, Jez moved to London, and Rory took over, travelling down from University in Leeds each weekend to play hundreds of gigs over the next couple of years. It’s not uncommon now to see power duos performing each weekend, but Tamarin may have been the band to start it all!*</p>
				<p><em>(*This may not be completely true.)</em></p>
			</div>
